            h2.section-heading Skeleton
            h2.subheading A dead simple, responsive boilerplate.
            p
              | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Skeleton is a boilerplate made for smaller projects that don’t need the weight of a full UI framework. It was built with mobile design in mind and its typography, 12 column fluid grid, and style work fantastic together.
            p
              | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The AngularJS library provides dozens of functions and directives to jumpstart your application. <b><em>Ng-app</em></b> provides module scope, <b><em>ng-init</em></b> to initialize javascript variables, and <b><em>ng-bind</em></b> for evaluating expressions, to name a few. In addition to what comes “out-of-the-box”, Angular’s community has produced numerous third party libraries making problem solving a google search away in most cases.
            h2.section-heading The A In MEAN
            img.img-responsive(src='img/mean.png', alt='')
            span.caption.text-muted
              | The MEAN stack.
            p
              | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Angular fits in nicely with the rest of the MEAN development stack because it is applicable to many common tasks and it is written in JavaScript. According to a recent survey of over 26k stackoverflow users, JavaScript has been the most widely used technology since 2014. With the recent development of server (express & NodeJS) and database (mongodb) technologies, it seems safe to assume this popularity will continue to grow, or at least maintain, for the next decade. 
            h2.section-heading Finally,
            p
              | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Angular is an attractive solution, however, a higher level of abstraction means limited functionality in some cases. Choosing the right framework is important when starting a large project and we'll be covering a few other frameworks, like #[a(href="react-blog-post") ReactJS], to help you make the right choice.
